        "content": "<p>We are looking out for codehilite color, more specifically color to highlight tagged lines in dark mode. More discussion <a href=\"https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/16984#issuecomment-786183721\">here</a>.<br>\nRight now, color for line highlight, in dark mode looks like:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/c8/upatuI6LHbIRYzR26NJW-qix/Broader_dark_hl_lines.png\">Dark Mode</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/c8/upatuI6LHbIRYzR26NJW-qix/Broader_dark_hl_lines.png\" title=\"Dark Mode\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/c8/upatuI6LHbIRYzR26NJW-qix/Broader_dark_hl_lines.png\"></a></div><p>Here highlighting color is almost invisible in dark mode.<br>\nWhile it looks good in day mode:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/5d/mH6dfq5jxmYCP8WUnygcsq-l/hl_lines_day_new.png\">Day Mode</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/5d/mH6dfq5jxmYCP8WUnygcsq-l/hl_lines_day_new.png\" title=\"Day Mode\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/5d/mH6dfq5jxmYCP8WUnygcsq-l/hl_lines_day_new.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 1128185,
        "sender_full_name": "Akshat",
        "timestamp": 1615063872
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Can someone please suggest, what should be the better choice of color here, in Dark Mode ?</p>",
        "id": 1128186,
        "sender_full_name": "Akshat",
        "timestamp": 1615063906
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I peeked in <a href=\"http://github.com\">github.com</a> and <a href=\"http://gitlab.com\">gitlab.com</a>. They use following in the dark mode:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/26/RsnIqbmxQrBZ6-tkMKg9aPYS/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-02-13-32.png\">GitHub</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/26/RsnIqbmxQrBZ6-tkMKg9aPYS/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-02-13-32.png\" title=\"GitHub\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/26/RsnIqbmxQrBZ6-tkMKg9aPYS/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-02-13-32.png\"></a></div><p><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/9/GaSrBKz76jO8qLbNJ8RBDxfJ/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-02-12-48.png\">GitLab</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/9/GaSrBKz76jO8qLbNJ8RBDxfJ/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-02-12-48.png\" title=\"GitLab\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/9/GaSrBKz76jO8qLbNJ8RBDxfJ/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-02-12-48.png\"></a></div><p>Probably, GitHub uses <code>#2a2519</code> (hex value) and GitLab uses <code>#373b41</code> (hex value)</p>",
        "id": 1128187,
        "sender_full_name": "Akshat",
        "timestamp": 1615063911
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Following is how it looks in case of:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/28/ru1vxy6VKf40Hd31aAYeJkCW/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-03-04-47.png\">GitHub Version</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/28/ru1vxy6VKf40Hd31aAYeJkCW/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-03-04-47.png\" title=\"GitHub Version\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/28/ru1vxy6VKf40Hd31aAYeJkCW/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-03-04-47.png\"></a></div><p><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/ed/93WOCWuUddIVOKA_hDf8S8Xj/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-03-05-22.png\">GitLab Version</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/ed/93WOCWuUddIVOKA_hDf8S8Xj/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-03-05-22.png\" title=\"GitLab Version\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/ed/93WOCWuUddIVOKA_hDf8S8Xj/Screenshot-from-2021-03-07-03-05-22.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 1128191,
        "sender_full_name": "Akshat",
        "timestamp": 1615066644
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I feel that the Github's color is somewhat better than Gitlab's one since there is a clear contrast between text and background but this doesn't seem to look very good with Zulip's default blue background. Maybe a little lighter shade of that may look better.</p>",
        "id": 1128216,
        "sender_full_name": "Gaurav Pandey (ligmitz)",
        "timestamp": 1615092997
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, I think the version with the GitLab color fits the rest of our colors better, so I think that's a passable option that'd make the feature mergeable; though I think it is worth playing with a color options as <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"17516\">Gaurav Pandey (ligmitz)</span> suggests.</p>",
